.Dd April 21, 2026
.Dt B76PIPE_STREAM 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm b76pipe_stream
.Nd streaming Base76 7-bit pipeline encoder/decoder
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm b76pipe_stream
.Op Fl r
.Op Fl v
.Op Fl i Ar file
.Op Fl o Ar file
.Op Fl - -alpha Ar file
.Op Fl - -selftest Op Ar string
.Op Ar message ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility implements a streaming, reversible Base76 7-bit binary pipeline
encoder and decoder.  It is part of the Willtech Base76 Pipeline Suite and is
designed for use with pipes, FIFOs, device files, and long-running streams
where output must be produced incrementally as input arrives.

.Pp
Unlike the non-streaming
.Xr b76pipe 3 ,
which buffers the entire input into a big integer before encoding,
.Nm
processes data byte-by-byte and emits output continuously.  The program
preserves deterministic forward and reverse semantics and includes a
comprehensive internal self-test facility.

.Sh MODES OF OPERATION
.Ss Forward Encoding (default)
Forward mode converts raw bytes into a two-stage Base76 representation:
.Bl -bullet
.It
Stage 1: each input byte is converted to a Base76 digit (0–75).
.It
Stage 2: each Base76 digit is expanded into a 7-bit sequence, and each bit is
encoded as a Base76 digit representing ASCII '0' (48) or '1' (49).
.El
.Pp
If
.Fl v
is specified, Stage 1 tokens are printed to
.Stderr ,
while Stage 2 output is streamed to
.Stdout
or to the file specified by
.Fl o .

.Ss Reverse Decoding
Reverse mode reconstructs the 7-bit bitstream from Stage 2 Base76 characters,
reassembles Stage 1 digits, and emits decoded bytes as soon as enough bits are
available to resolve a byte.  Whitespace in the encoded stream is ignored.

.Sh ALPHABET HANDLING
The Base76 alphabet consists of 76 unique 7-bit characters.  The default
alphabet is compiled into the binary via
.Pa base76_alphabet.h .

.Pp
A custom alphabet may be loaded using:
.Pp
.Dl --alpha file
.Pp
The loader applies the following rules:
.Bl -bullet
.It
Only 7-bit characters (0–127) are considered.
.It
Whitespace is ignored.
.It
Duplicate characters are ignored.
.It
The first 76 unique characters encountered form the alphabet.
.It
If fewer than 76 unique characters are found, the program exits with an error.
.El

.Sh SELF-TEST FACILITY
The
.Fl -selftest
option performs deterministic forward and reverse validation.  Self-test always
exits after completion and never continues into normal pipeline operation.

.Pp
The following modes are supported:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -selftest
Use the built-in diagnostic message and exit.
.It Fl -selftest Ar string
Use the provided string as test input and exit.
.It Fl -selftest Fl i Ar file
Use the contents of
.Ar file
as test input and exit.
.It Fl -selftest Fl i Ar file Fl o Ar file
Run the full internal self-test, then:
.Bl -bullet
.It
forward-encode the input file to the specified output file,
.It
reverse-decode the output file,
.It
compare the decoded data to the original input,
.It
exit with success or failure.
.El
.El

.Pp
Self-test always writes:
.Bl -bullet
.It
.Pa .b76pipe_stream.selftest.i
(original input)
.It
.Pa .b76pipe_stream.selftest.o
(encoded Stage 2 output)
.El

.Pp
It is an error to specify both a self-test string and
.Fl i .

.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl i Ar file
Read input from
.Ar file .
If omitted, input is read from standard input.
.It Fl o Ar file
Write output to
.Ar file .
If omitted, output is written to standard output.
.It Fl r
Reverse (decode) mode.
.It Fl v
Verbose mode.  Print Stage 1 Base76 tokens to
.Stderr .
.It Fl - -alpha Ar file
Load a custom Base76 alphabet.
.It Fl - -selftest Op Ar string
Run internal forward/reverse validation and exit.
.It Fl h , Fl - -help
Display usage information.
.It Fl - -version
Display program version.
.El

.Sh STREAMING BEHAVIOUR
.Nm
does not buffer the entire input and is safe for use with:
.Bl -bullet
.It
pipes
.It
FIFOs
.It
device files (e.g.\& Pa /dev/tty , Pa /dev/random )
.It
long-running producers
.El
Output is emitted as soon as enough data is available to produce the next
token or byte.

.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It 0
Success.
.It 1
Error in input, alphabet, self-test, or pipeline operation.
.El

.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa .b76pipe_stream.selftest.i
Self-test input file.
.It Pa .b76pipe_stream.selftest.o
Self-test encoded output file.
.El

.Sh EXAMPLES
Encode a file:
.Pp
.Dl $ b76pipe_stream -i message.bin -o message.b76
.Pp
Decode a Base76 file:
.Pp
.Dl $ b76pipe_stream -r -i message.b76 -o message.bin
.Pp
Verbose Stage 1 output:
.Pp
.Dl $ b76pipe_stream -v -i input.bin
.Pp
Run self-test with custom input:
.Pp
.Dl $ b76pipe_stream --selftest "Hello Base76"
.Pp
Run full file-based self-test:
.Pp
.Dl $ b76pipe_stream --selftest -i data.bin -o encoded.txt

